Basic setting  Setup guide for raspberry pi  Auto-start Use sudo crontab -e to set autostart programme
@reboot python /home/pi/MyScript.py &amp;  This tells Cron that every boot (or reboot or start-up) we want to run Python with the script MyScript.py. The &ldquo;&amp;&rdquo; at the end of the line means the command is run in the background and it won&rsquo;t stop the system booting up as before.
